<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
As this is my first post on this site, I will do my best to make it brief  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">. <BR>1. I feel that the price increase, although a little high, is waranted as we have never had an increase before. Perhaps by raising only $1 to 2$ wouldn't have made as much waves, but I can see why it was done. <BR>2. What I would expect from eq for my increased rate:<BR>a. I have seen a lot of great things come for those who are higher levels. The alternate advancements, and the higher level zones are great for those who are that high. But my highest character after playing EQ for over 2 years is level 39. Most of my characters are less than 20. I would love to have more content added for 15 to 30 levels.<BR>b. increase customer support hours either in either phone support or online at the Tech area on the chat rooms. Unless they have changed them from last time I was there, I had to take off of work to get ahold of a live body for answers.<BR>c. Bring back more quests for lower levels. You have been adding so much for higher levels, the sometimes it feels like you have forgotten the "newbies" it's a great start you have done. Keep it coming  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>All in all, though, I feel that even after my 2 years of playing (friendly playing, not Gotta level, gotta level) I still have fun playing this game and will continue to do so as much as I can.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> Thanks for your ear.
</FONT>
