I have been playing EQ for 2 years now and while there are many things about the game at I like, there are also things that bother me.  One of these things is the lack of dynamic/GM quests that occur (at least while I'm playing...)  If Verant is going to raise the price for EQ, the service that they provide should also increase.  I understand that the staffing is just not present for dynamic quests to occur on every server, every day, but there could be much more of an effort made to implement dynamic quests into the game.  Having a time set aside every week, (say 2-3 hours on a given day) for a GM quest would dramatically improve the atmosphere of the game.  These quests could follow a script that the developers come up with and continue with the story each week in sort of a serial format.  I'm sure that there are many players that love this sort of thing and it would at least offer something new for players sick of camping mobs for hours on end...
</FONT>
