I think I should agree with Mr_Kite. Although a payrate increase may be warrented, let's face facts. How many people out there with hundreds of hours of gameplay on a character ( or even spread between multiple characters ) want to loose the time and effort that was spent creating said character(s). In this respect, the userbase is being extorted. No, they will not give up something they've invested not only they're $9.00 / month into, but also they're freetime, they're energy, and they're personalities. Because of the nature of RPG's in general, players grow accustomed to characters they create, and that attachment is akin to that of a pet, or at least a very passonate hobby. The pay increase isn't massive, but it is a trap of sorts. My only question is ( and granted, Cost of living considered ) what exactly have you ( VI ) added reciently over what you've had in the past that makes it imperative that you increase the rate? Let's face facts...all signs show that your userbase is growing massivly thanks to SoL, and soon for PoP. With this many new users, all paying the said $9.00 / Month, and with a previous statement about legends ( I'll quote as close as I can "There's only 1 full time GM per blue server, where legends has 14"), I don't see where you're adding new people to the servers to help the playerbase. As for the "We have more content to observe, watch, modify, etc", that shouldn't be an issue, given that older content ( Antonica, Odis, Faedwar ) should be fine. The newer content ( Warrens / Hole, Kunark, Velios, Luclin ) should all be on a relative incline towards good working content, so there shouldn't be any need to keep extra people working on that over what you had when said expansions came out and the "Old World" needed to be fixed. Following this model, I would expect to see Warrens / Hole, Kunark, and most of Velios totally fixed and 85% - 99% bugfree by the release of PoP. In which case, your people working on these problems can move to Luclin / PoP, and STILL, no need for pay increase. <P>OK, here's what I see that you would need the pay increase for.<P>1. New servers. Hardware / Software<BR>2. New CS ( 1 per server ) for new servers<BR>3. Bandwith, and lot's of it<BR>4. Cost of living for your people <BR>4a. This should be covered with the increase in the player base<P>What I want more than anything right now is a fairly detailed description of EXACTLY why they need the extra money.<P>$2.00 / month * 10000 players = $20,000.00 / month more than previously.  What costs $20,000 / Month? That's what I'm asking. ( Modify numbers to closer reflect actual game statisticts, being that the usercount was removed from the client )<P>Don't get me wrong, I'm not saying it's not warrented, and hell, you may have some very valid reasons for doing it...but you've gotta tell us. You can't just say "we said so" and leave it at that. That gives a really bad Microsoft attitude, and everyone knows how the majority of people feel about microsoft. <P>Anyway, that's my 2cp<P>--------------------<P>..."Live to play, or get out of the way!!!"...
