The thing that upsets me even more is the fact that I myself have never directly benefitted of any of their "new stuff." I'm still waiting on the "old stuff" to be fixed!<P>1. My computer won't take SoL so I guess I'm SOL as it were. (I had one that had MORE than the spec's required and it had some kind of problem with SoL but it got totally fried.)<BR>3. I'm almost totally caster oriented so I benefited very little from the plethora of new items and infact suffered under the already screwed up economy of Prexus.<BR>4. All these new high level oriented events on the normal servers have mostly been an under-mid slaughter fest, much to the ire of THREE of my lower level casters.<BR>5. I hardly ever call the GM, mostly you can find info you want on such sites as Castersrealm and when you do(at least in my case) it almost seems like the <B>Guide</B>you get doesn't even know his own class.<BR>6. I really could have lived without SoL and will be able to live without this new Planes of Power depending on its requirements(it says they will not change but change from what? SoL or the EQ before SoL?), I don't see much that they are offering me other than more grief.<BR>7. As said before, there are still a ton of problems with the current EQ and no clear info on what the devil is happening and what is not happening.<BR>8. In relation to the above, we simply do not get enough information to decide for sure what is what. Not until its loaded into our laps at least.<BR>9. I'm presuming Legends didn't work out, and I didn't sign up for it either. Any added costs they had for that I really don't think is my problem.<BR>10. SoL is infact going to hurt me auction-wise as I will not be able to access this "wonderful" bazaar, which isn't even finished yet.<P>   Finally, 30% is a very very LARGE increase in anything, particularly in those cases where people have multiple accounts. I mean, you got along apparently well enough with what we were giving you until all this new stuff came out, which as I stated above, I got nothing of value out of. Did you add CR's and design teams or something since then to add to or fix the game <B>I</B>play?<BR>Maybe you should charge depending on what expansions each account has activated or something.<P>Basically your going to charge me more and leave me hanging here with a .txt message reading:<BR>"TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN:<BR>        I. O. U.<BR>                 Sincerely, SOE<BR>P.S. We're going to go ahead and charge you some more money ok? And no, you don't need to know what for."<P>  <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"><P>**Note** This may be a bit incoherent, I've got the English down mostly in vocabulary and spellings and such but I still have a tendency to ramble on and on. Please feel free to e-mail me to correct or refine my grammar!<P>P.S. I'm not saying its necessarily a bad thing, I know of a couple of MMORPG's that charge this much, I'd just like to know that MY game is getting its fair share of this money instead of getting put on the "backburner" as it were.
