<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Its really just simple business sense.<P>Raise prices for 2000 users on legends by $30 a month. This lands them an extra $60,000 per month (though I am just guessing as to the # of players on legends, may be less than 2000). Legends doesn't give them any extra profit, just extra revenue.<P>Raise prices for 400,000 users by $3 per month. End result, an extra $1.2 Million per month, and they don't even need 2 dedicated GM teams for each standard server.<P>Actually though, the rate increase doesn't really bother me, but I think they should've been raising it by $1 per year, not $3 at once. I think they were a little too proud of that 989 moniker.....  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> <P>I am a little worried about the future of EQ, as we are completely dependant on VI to provide service in order to play. <P>I guess what I would like to see in return for this price increase is some sort of contingency plan: <BR>How long will they keep the game going?<BR>Whats the plan as they eventually have to phase out servers? Will transfers for continuing subscribers be free?<P>I just worry that EQ has now hit 'Cash Cow' status for SOE, and they may be trying to milk it for all they can as they get ready for new games launching this year.<P>In the technology world, 3 years is an eternity, I'd hope they are thinking of using some of this money to upgrade equipment in some of the servers that have been around for a while.....<P>Oh well, just a few thoughts, but this should give enough fodder to keep people going for a while  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Naladini
