30% increase in price.<P>Say the average person at EQ earns US$75 000 pa and there are 50 of them.  Their wages would be covered in less than one month's subscription.  Say on costs and servers etc cost 6 times the costs of wages, that leaves US $24 000 000 for profits and development.  And that assumes that the 50 people working on the game are not part of the development process for new content.<P>Under these circumstances I would like to have at least the following.<P>- That extra content that they are making be given to us, rather than having to pay extra for it with expansion packs.<BR>- 24hr Gm representation.  <BR>- Better patching and integration of new content <BR>  1) That they don't require several months to implement expansions, but spend more time testing and fixing bugs before hand.<BR>  2) That with so many patches happening they break the patching into 2 groups of servers so that we can all continue to play on a different servers as our main server is patched.
