<IMG SRC="http://forums.crgaming.com/eq/profile.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for Daeryen"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://" target=_new><IMG SRC="http://forums.crgaming.com/eq/homepage.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Author's Homepage"></A> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.crgaming.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=private_message&u=00025563"><IMG SRC="http://forums.crgaming.com/eq/priv_message.gif" BORDER='0' ALT="Send New Private Message"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.crgaming.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=3&t=002814&reply_num=000034&u=00025563"><IMG SRC="http://forums.crgaming.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.crgaming.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=3&t=002814&replyto=000034"><IMG SRC="http://forums.crgaming.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Never thought I'd say this, but I actually miss the days when EQ even had a "vision."  I kept fairly up to date via castersrealm, and every change or refused change was made to maintain the balance of power between players.  Changes were slow and often not what we wanted, but I could see that Verant cared about how the game was played.  Now Verant seems to be going Roman- Give the people what they want!  Or think they want.  Verant is acting like it desperately needs to entice people to stay with the game.  Make more content to keep them happy! Eliminate some old inconveniences to fatten them up!  CS is pitiful (go ask the GM-bot in chat about not being able to log in any time).  Existing content is buggy and incomplete, why the hell are they making more?  Up till now I've been content to sit, pay my 10 bucks, and wait for something better.  Now I'm seeing Verant and game quality going downhill, with no sign of improvements.  There's always been the hope that, maybe they'll fix all the bugs after they finish with Kunark/Velious/Luclin/etc.  Now they're just moving on and making more and not fixing what they've done wrong.  If I saw Verant working to actually improve the game, to flush out the bugs and improve/rebalance old quests, I would stick with them.  But there's no sign that they're going to change their ways and they don't have any faith or commitment from me. Charging more money for such lousy service is just too much to put up with.  I will be retiring my characters and returning to Daggerfall (anyone remember that one?  ahhh the good ol' days) while I wait for Morrowind to release.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
